# Manual HTTP calls for the Excel export — these hit the RUNNING app (dev database).
# Pick the "dev" environment. The flow is asynchronous:
#   1) POST /export -> 202 + report id (captured below)
#   2) GET /reports/{id} -> status; with the worker running it is already "completed"
#   3) GET /reports/{id}/download -> saves the .xlsx to disk
# The email (with the download link) lands in Mailpit: http://localhost:8025
# Seed some assigned candidatures first (see http/consolidated-listing.http) so the report has rows.

### 1) Request an export (default: years_of_experience desc) -> 202, capture the id
POST {{baseUrl}}/candidatures/consolidated/export
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{}

> {% client.global.set("report_id", response.body.data.id); %}

### 2) Poll status -> with the worker running, this is already "completed" (has download_url)
GET {{baseUrl}}/reports/{{report_id}}
Accept: application/json

### 3) Download the .xlsx -> PhpStorm saves it under http/generated/ and opens it
GET {{baseUrl}}/reports/{{report_id}}/download
Accept: application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.spreadsheetml.sheet

>>! generated/report.xlsx

### Export filtered by evaluator name prefix (only that evaluator's candidates)
POST {{baseUrl}}/candidatures/consolidated/export
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{ "sort": "evaluator_name", "direction": "asc", "filter": { "evaluator_name": "M" } }

> {% client.global.set("filtered_report_id", response.body.data.id); %}

### Status of the filtered export
GET {{baseUrl}}/reports/{{filtered_report_id}}
Accept: application/json

### Invalid sort column (expect 422)
POST {{baseUrl}}/candidatures/consolidated/export
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{ "sort": "drop_table" }

### Status of a well-formed but non-existent report id (expect 404)
GET {{baseUrl}}/reports/01ARZ3NDEKTSV4RRFFQ69G5FAV
Accept: application/json

### Download a non-existent report (expect 404)
GET {{baseUrl}}/reports/01ARZ3NDEKTSV4RRFFQ69G5FAV/download
Accept: application/json


# =====================================================================
# See the lifecycle states in slow motion (pending -> completed):
#   docker compose stop worker      # nobody drains the queue
#   run the POST below -> GET status stays "pending"/"processing"
#   docker compose start worker     # the worker picks it up
#   GET status again -> "completed"
# =====================================================================

### Export while the worker is stopped -> stays pending until you start the worker
POST {{baseUrl}}/candidatures/consolidated/export
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{}

> {% client.global.set("slow_report_id", response.body.data.id); %}

### Status (pending/processing while worker is down; completed once it is back up)
GET {{baseUrl}}/reports/{{slow_report_id}}
Accept: application/json
